reviews.review_text:
Dick's Picks 13 Big fan of this show, from start to finish. First set is well-played and I absolutely adore the song selection. Rockin' Getaway->GSET opener, LIG->Deal closer, and check out the other Garcia tunes: TLEO, Jack-A-Roe, Dire Wolf, BRB. Has a real old school, sort of folksy feel to it. Then comes the second set. Every relisten is better than the last. Cannot get enough of the massive He's Gone and really the entirety of Dick's Disc 3 is top-notch. Any era.   

Here's some of what Latvala had to say: "This is the one! It contains one of the best and most thrilling jams in the last 15 years.... [After] He's Gone... we get something that I don't believe has ever occurred before: a pure jam that lasts about 15-20 minutes and contains the most unbelievable playing."
